
### Pin strategy

Use minor version ranges per `docs/DESIGN_PRINCIPLES.md` compatibility matrix (e.g., `>=0.4.0,<0.5`). No lockfile: allows automatic patch updates while reproducible via ranges.

### Noise handling

False positives are assessed using the framework in `docs/DEPENDENCY_AUDIT.md`. Document accepted risks before overriding CI.

### CI integration

The `supply-chain` job (matrixed across Python 3.11/3.12) runs `pip-audit --desc --severity-high` on every push/PR to `master`. Fails on high-severity issues.

### Upgrade policy

- Monitor upstream (`replayt`, `langgraph`) changelogs.
- Test minor bumps locally (update range, re-run audits/tests).
- Widen ranges in `pyproject.toml` after verification; update compatibility matrix/docs.
